name: guaiacol carbonate
Reason: The basic unit for comparison here could be phenol, which has a melting point of 41°C. Guaiacol contains two methoxy groups and a carbonate bridge relative to phenol. Each methoxy group would increase the melting point due to the introduction of stronger intermolecular forces, such as dipole-dipole interactions. Estimating a +20°C increase per methoxy group. The carbonate bridge links two phenolic rings, potentially raising the melting point further due to the increased rigidity and planarity of the molecule. This could add another +30°C. Combining these, we predict a total increase of 70°C from the base value of phenol.
